    <note type="biography">
        <p>Barrister and writer on elocution. Called to the bar, 1844. Established the Public Reading Society between 1850 and 1860. Lectured on elocution at universities and theological colleges; lecturer on elocution at Oxford and King’s College, London.</p></note>
